Action log settings are used for to keep track of actions performed by various users in the system.All actions will be recorded in a log file.

In  order to change the Action log settings in Plesk, first login to your Plesk administrative panel as admin and do the following steps:

1) Select Settings tab from the Home page and then click on Action Log.
